studio lecture series al souza studio lecture series al souza facebook twitter email print add to calendar texas based artist al souza will discuss and present samples of his work over the last 35 years he has a very active national and international exhibition record highlighted by inclusion in biennials at the whitney museum of american art the sao paulo international biennale and the venice biennale he has had more than 100 solo exhibitions in the united states and europe initially trained as a civil engineer souza received his mfa in 1972 from the university of massachusetts amherst and is teaching at the university of houston school of art when thursday november 11 2010 5 30 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where cummings art building ar2 map audience faculty staff general public students tags lecture reading visual arts sponsor department of art & art history contact 650 723 3404 risip stanford edu admission free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 256 25673 more info last modified november 10 2010
